<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_3fd58744-c0d5-48a9-9e55-ccc13225ffcf" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="VIC"><sptc>E4P1</sptc><title id="_64319154-926c-4fc1-a95d-65af6b83848c">Surface drainage systems</title><archive-num>2019: FP2.1</archive-num><subclause id="_ca43accf-dd8f-4d67-851c-296c85268d7b" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_a83f56c8-32be-4e04-a25f-9d1097c65e0a">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A surface drainage system must dispose of stormwater flows from rainfall events having an average recurrence interval appropriate to:</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_03fda39f-e9f5-43e4-8fa1-9d986c23eb7a">The importance of the building.</li><li id="_bfdd4f2e-a9a0-4254-ab97-24df2c0e25c6">The severity of potential damage to property, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1362_2.0.0.xml#_ba5bd5ee-ef5f-41be-b153-43835028cd86" id="_05a9ef2a-085d-4c93-b644-8e71a9a784c2" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">loss</xref> of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1186_0.6.0.xml#_905252bf-2ff1-43f8-ae81-2949aa116fee" id="_cdb6ab23-eefb-4258-82e2-070a44e15cb3" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">amenity</xref>, illness or injury that would result from the failure of the system.</li></ol></subclause></clause>